(221, 1, '2017-08-18 10:17:47', '2017-08-18 10:17:47', '<!-- wp:fl-builder/layout -->\n<h1>\n					They are <br>our passion\n				</h1>\n	<h3>\n					How it started\n				</h3>\n			<p>We helped road side children and start donating food, dress and many more things. we started to teach uneducated children. then we all gave our little contribution to establish our non profitable organization.</p>		\n	<h3>\n					Our passion\n				</h3>\n			<p>We discovered it three years ago. Ever since, we’ve spent every day working and finding our place in the collective efforts to end extreme poverty.</p>		\n	<h3>\n					Know process\n				</h3>\n			<p>Starting an NGO requires more than just money. It requires hard work, determination, and a genuine desire to support others. To start and run an NGO is an almost similar process to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.shethepeople.tv/news/the-woman-who-leads-the-kinetic-motor-company-sulajja-firodia-motwani/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">run a company</a>, but here you have to keep transparency. Moreover, here you have to work for the welfare of the society without expecting any profit.</p>		\n	<h2>\n					Team that provides <br>loving care\n				</h2>\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/SAVE_20190309_175959.jpeg\" alt=\"SAVE_20190309_175959\" itemprop=\"image\">\n	<h3>\n					Sonika Gupta\n				</h3>\n			<p>FOUNDER</p>		\n	<p>Starting a non-profit can be an extremely rewarding entrepreneurial experience. It\'s a beautiful thing, but it takes a lot more than passion and heart. A non-profit gives you the ability to give back to your community and really make a difference unlike any other industry.</p>\n	<h3>\n					Our members\n				</h3>\n			<p>Rajeev Gupta, Sangeeta Gupta,Aman Gupta, Siwangi Gupta.</p>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/Pet-services-21-free-img.jpg\" alt=\"Team\" itemprop=\"image\">\n<!-- /wp:fl-builder/layout -->', 'Who we are', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'who-we-are', '', '', '2019-07-21 21:46:20', '2019-07-21 21:46:20', '', 0, 'https://websitedemos.net/pet-services-free/?page_id=221', 0, 'page', '', 0),
(223, 1, '2017-08-18 10:18:51', '2017-08-18 10:18:51', '<!-- wp:fl-builder/layout -->\n	<h1>\n					creating health,<br> happiness and hope\n				</h1>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_2fVZ7C.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_2fVZ7C\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>our home</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>We believe that every child deserves to be safe and cared for so the homes are the bedrock of our charity. It is here that the children experience, possibly for the first time in their lives, a secure, stable and nurturing environment among people on whom they can depend.</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_4PTDbP.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_4PTDbP\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>medicare and nurition</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>When children arrive at our charity from the streets or slums they are malnourished and many are ill. Weakness, scabies, boils, skin diseases, burns, infections, diarrhoea, tuberculosis, typhoid, STDs, leprosy, neurological problems and addiction are all conditions from which children may suffer. Treating these and maintaining good health are important to enable the children to take part in school.</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_7Lw3Ht.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_7Lw3Ht\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>our school</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>Education is a human right but one that millions of children are still denied. By providing underprivileged children with an education at our school we give them the key to unlock opportunity; a chance to get a decent job, to escape poverty and to support their families &amp; communities.</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_9iUOKE.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_9iUOKE\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>Extra Curricular Activities & Sport</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>At our charity we continually expose our children to a positive all round education, build up their confidence and determination to take on learning challenges and to view Future Hope as a steppingstone to a brighter, self-reliant future. As they discover new activities and talents we see an increase in their self-esteem, motivation and sense of belonging.</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_6qLOK7.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_6qLOK7\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>Career Guidance & Higher Education</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>The ultimate goal for our charity is to see the children in its care flourish and become independent, self-sufficient adults. Therefore, supporting the transition from education to further study and employment is essential to our success.</p>\n	<ul>\n		<li>		\n				<img src=\"http://localhost/ngowebsite/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/LogoMakr_9sxmri.png\" alt=\"LogoMakr_9sxmri\" itemprop=\"image\"/>\n		<h4>impact</h4 ><p></p></li>	</ul>\n	<p>Over 3 years the charity has touched more than 500 young lives and many hundreds more families. We pride ourselves on our alumni who have become self-reliant, hardworking members of society, with steady employment and happy families.</p>\n<!-- /wp:fl-builder/layout -->', 'Services we provide', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'services-we-provide', '', '', '2020-02-10 05:43:33', '2020-02-10 05:43:33', '', 221, 'https://websitedemos.net/pet-services-free/?page_id=223', 0, 'page', '', 0),
